# zSpace Blog Generation — Environment Configuration
#
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
#  ACCESS TOKENS
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
#  The blog workflow needs two Directus API tokens:
#
#    DIRECTUS_TOKEN_SANDBOX     -> sandbox1.admin.zspace.com (safe to test against)
#    DIRECTUS_TOKEN_PRODUCTION  -> admin.zspace.com (the live site)
#
#  These are "Blog Writer" scoped tokens (create/update on mkt_blog and the
#  category junction table). They are NOT admin tokens.
#
#  Token owner (Directus user) for both environments:
#    api-blog-writer@zspace.com
#  To rotate a token, log into Directus admin as that user (or as a Directus
#  admin) and regenerate the API token on that user's profile.
#
#  How to get them:
#    Ask JP Donnelly (jdonnelly@zspace.com) to issue you a pair of blog-writer
#    tokens. Tokens are per-user — don't share yours, and don't commit them
#    anywhere. The `.env` file you create from this template is gitignored.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------

# Active environment: set to "sandbox" or "production"
# Start with "sandbox" for your first blog.
DIRECTUS_ENV=sandbox

# Sandbox (sandbox1.admin.zspace.com) — safe to test against
# Token belongs to: api-blog-writer@zspace.com
DIRECTUS_URL_SANDBOX=https://sandbox1.admin.zspace.com
DIRECTUS_TOKEN_SANDBOX=

# Production (admin.zspace.com) — publishes to the live site
# Token belongs to: api-blog-writer@zspace.com
DIRECTUS_URL_PRODUCTION=https://admin.zspace.com
DIRECTUS_TOKEN_PRODUCTION=

# Add more environments as needed:
# DIRECTUS_URL_STAGING=https://staging.admin.zspace.com
# DIRECTUS_TOKEN_STAGING=
